{
  "stem": "18102.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he would have us huddle near the door of the vestibule in the brick building so that we could quickly run through the door if anything hit the building.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I do recall-- I have a vivid memory of us huddling in, in, in silence as the bombs fell around us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was at that moment that I experienced for the very first time my own fright because, at that point, I understood that if something hits this building, no good would come of this.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- it was the first sort of awakening that war was a dangerous thing for me personally.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you could read it on their face.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was, this was a, a horror for them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There is no way you can describe the change in a person's face and demeanor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That normalcy had left forever.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was no longer a concern about what you eat or what you don't eat, what I leave on, on the plate that I didn't eat.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The concern now for-- was for physical safety and that the family should hang together, and we shouldn't be apart or be caught in the streets alone or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was a great deal of concern, and everybody tried to stay together.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as I said, until my father left, we were always together inside the house and mostly inside the house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody wanted anybody to leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Any of the bombing or the strafing, was that near enough for you to see or did you just hear it?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I could just hear it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It wasn't until later that I saw bombed-out buildings.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
